snippet.textDisplay:
I've actually had my hair be a bright turquoise a few times, and it took me months for the color to fade into mint green. My hair had to be bleached into almost white for the shade to be pure. I never had to make a new appointment to enhance the color, because I just let it grow out. The pace that the color fades at is quite dependent on how often the hair is washed.

(I've also had random hairs pierce my skin sometimes)

But no seriously, I’ve dyed it a number of times (green, bright purple, natural red, blonde ends, copper highlights, light blue, etc) because naturally it’s frizzy, thick and light brown. Also have had it super long, as a pixie cut, shoulder length and am considering an undercut when I get bored of it again - because I always do.
